The paper discusses the use of bibliometric parameters and automatic tools to evaluate the productivity and impact of research units in Portugal. This suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of digital libraries (cs.DL), computational complexity (cs.CY), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
